so is sold for, so that will prove badd £26:6:2 of lieven verooten

rander gugkt & £2:13:8 by hiliphf rancois de behaat de mons, so
that I see butt little hopes to recover & any thingh of all boubt itt all
abad debt, butt for that you can not blame mee, as yett I have mads
no bad bebts, butt on my side, for which god be thanckes butt if
the french should prevaill up on us I know nothow all things could
fall out: the 5 packes of cottons are well arrived Dayly here expected
butt yd invoyce tarryes to long, for I can sell now withrat itt
as for TH as soone the varantie is past wee will be upon him againe
& give you the advise of the succes & mmilst I remain

London mr. Abram Tivian
mij last to you was on the 9 rutt to which please to be refferred sence reed.
yd of p deste, tis well that you shall in order the desired bayes & because ours do go
of here a race, so desire you to in onder to or 50 bayes more assorted, from 36 tot6 ƒ
de peece, butt lett no more mr. chipping middle with any, because I must have
an acnd. of every pack particular: inclosed you have the note under my ocone
hand of the bayes I receaved, & no more wee ought so pay, for itt is not my
mistate, & the packts have no where been opened butt in my owne house. I have
given you creditt for my half share in the bale N.42 in which N441. is to reddisch
& 433 to extravagant nott att all to the patt. sent whoever God sending then
will over, hope to sell them to content, I am told that smith will be ready to
saile from sHull vere speedly, because Pindar lest a good deale behinde, so I hope
that the rest of our goods will come safe with him, seeng there are few or no
white grayes to be hadd in the markett, so you have don well to gett thim to be made
I have recd the packes out of Pindar, & compared them by the invoyces, & do no
where finde the bale N37, so please to advise mee of any such numberbe
made up: I am sensible, thatt you have not that suply, which yd. occasions dosacqiun
yett I do finde that Included the bale N.42 you ave not £25- s in disbours for my
acctt where to the contrary I am much more in disbours y. acctt with
yd. lase bill of £200- wel £340- butt now the season comts on that sale is
alive, & hanvest past, shall bring us mony plintie, whilst never the less
the first I can gett shall be for you, because I must have all advantages in
the northren tradethat can by be exspected, I hope to see you here af so one
as the goods are shipt, for then you sall have bitt lillle to do in our concerne
& exspect that others of yd ow ne will not detaine you, & so with kinde saluts
@ 16 suynst 17
London Henry maynard -
Sr. sence my last to you of 9 curitt recd. yd of P ditto Ben klarck
is well arrived: and the goods come with pindar from hich are with mee
now I have given you creditt for my half share in the 3 packes aboard
John Collinier as soone as the super fijn cloathes be ready, lett them
come forward, as for the wrapping of our packes. I lett n welf do as
he thinckes fitt, butt for my past when you comply to my directions
you shall finde never complaints butt to pay 44 a 44:6 for bayes
in london where these you send from the north att 39 are much bettes
I will not meddle rith you says something of late of their breath
them you sent from London att 43 a 44 are scarey ⅓ of ayd broades
them you from hull 39 are thicher & well ⅓ of a yd broad which is much
in bayes - butt when you here shall shew you the difference: by the
last of mr. Scawen he told mee he would pay you without faile
when you meet the opportuintie to buy ½ worster frises of adrap
cullours as the last buy them in yd next pray note the prijse of FF
yallow marck pack writes haveing non by mee att present I hope you
shall speedly be suplyed with the G.N silver merck I want 5 pack
whites of about £25:- the 5p: if you finde some where arn
hazard to gett 5 suck pr please to do itt & send them to mee, as so one
as this comes to yd hand, order in the north the providing of 50 o168
whiter mant heften sayes assorted in prijses
